## ğŸ“ Overview
This project extracts text from images using **OCR (Optical Character Recognition)** and converts it into natural-sounding speech.  
Built as an accessibility solution for **visually impaired users** and general users who need hands-free reading.

## ğŸš€ Features
- Extracts text from any image (PNG, JPG, Scanned documents)
- Uses **Tesseract OCR** for accurate text recognition
- Converts text to speech using **gTTS**
- Supports multiple languages
- Simple and clean UI (if GUI is used)
- Saves audio output as `.mp3`

## ğŸ§  Tech Stack
- Python  
- OpenCV  
- Pytesseract (OCR)  
- gTTS (Text-to-Speech)  

## ğŸ“‚ Project Flow
1. Load Image  
2. Preprocess (grayscale, thresholding, noise removal)  
3. Run through OCR  
4. Convert extracted text â†’ audio  
5. Save or play audio  

